<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1626,2011]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,151,1184]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1626,1651]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[383,491,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 − 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1528,1551]" captionTargetBox="[183,1400,196,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 − 9. Adults of Lasiochira spp. 4. L. jianfengensis sp. nov., holotype, male; 5. Head of L. jianfengensis sp. nov., paratype, female; 6. L. jiulongshana sp. nov., holotype, male; 7. L. pallidiptera sp. nov., holotype, male; 8. L. taiwanensis sp. nov., holotype, male; 9. L. taiwanensis sp. nov., paratype, female. (Scales: 4, 6 – 9 = 2.0 mm; 5 = 0.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286108/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">
Figs. 
<number box="[447,491,1627,1651]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" value="8.9">8, 9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wing expanse 13.0−15.0 mm. Head creamy. Labial palpus white, second segment tinged with yellowish brown, third segment with a broad deep yellowish brown ring at distal 
<number box="[1233,1244,1663,1687]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1256,1271,1663,1687]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" value="3.0">3</number>
. Antenna pale yellowish brown, pecten length about 1.5 times width of scape. Thorax and tegula creamy, thorax with three pale yellowish brown bands at basal 
<number box="[507,517,1735,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[528,545,1735,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" value="4.0">4</number>
, at distal 
<number box="[651,665,1734,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[674,687,1734,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" value="5.0">5</number>
and before apex respectively. Forewing with costal margin slightly arched, apex triangularly protruding, termen oblique; ground color pale ocherous brown, paler between fold and dorsum, yellow on apical area; N-shaped pattern creamy, running from basal 
<number box="[1011,1025,1806,1831]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1034,1047,1806,1831]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" value="5.0">5</number>
of costal margin obliquely ventrad to before lower angle of cell, then arched obliquely up-outward to before end of costal margin and slightly expanded costal margin, finally arched ventrad to before ventro-apex; first stripe edged with black scales on inner margin medially, erect scale tufts indistinct; between first and second stripes yellow on costal margin, with a brown patch bearing a white dot at middle between upper corner of two stripes; second stripe edged with black scales medially on its outer margin; between second and third stripes with an ill-defined brown patch; a blackish brown spot at ventro-apex, on outer margin of third stripe; distinct scale tufts at 
<number box="[987,1000,151,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[1010,1023,151,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
of fold and at distal 
<number box="[1264,1274,151,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1285,1300,151,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
above fold; fringe golden yellow basally, white tinged greyish brown distally. Hindwing dark brown; fringe deep greyish yellow. Legs pale ocherous brown tinged with white scales; tarsi with white at apex of each segment dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[380,466,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 − 19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1864,1887]" captionTargetBox="[231,1415,224,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[180,1465,193,1874]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14 − 19. Male Genitalia of Lasiochira spp. 14. L. jianfengensis sp. nov., holotype, slide no. YAH 13037; 15. L. jiulongshana sp. nov., holotype, slide no. YAH 13032; 16. L. pallidiptera sp. nov., holotype, slide no. YAH 13043; 17. L. taiwanensis sp. nov., holotype, slide no. YAH 13045; 18. L. camaropa Meyrick, 1931; 19. L. xanthacma (Meyrick, 1938), slide no. YAH 13035. (Scales = 0.5 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286110/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[435,466,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). Uncus broad at base, gradually narrowed to about 
<number box="[1073,1086,260,285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[1097,1111,260,285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
, distal 
<number box="[1196,1210,260,285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1219,1232,260,285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
nearly parallel to blunt apex. Gnathos somewhat beak-like, broad at base, narrowed to hooked apex; lateral arms narrowly banded. Valva short and broad, sub-rectangular, apex bluntly truncate; costa nearly straight; ventral margin semicircularly concave beyond end of sacculus, distally protruding and arched. Sacculus with basal half uniformly narrow, distal half widened and forming a broad triangular process directing downward. Vinculum narrowly banded. Saccus broad, triangular. Juxta sub-square, anterior margin concave medially, posterior margin shallowly concave widely, forming a pair of thumb-like lateral lobes, lateral margin concave medially. Aedeagus stout, tubular, slightly shorter than valva, roundly protruding distally; cornuti consisting of three to four large sclerotized, irregular plates.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[409,497,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 − 26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1871,1894]" captionTargetBox="[302,1301,204,1800]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[266,1320,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20 − 26. Female Genitalia of Lasiochira spp. 20. L. jianfengensis sp. nov., paratype, slide no. YAH 13040; 21. L. jiulongshana sp. nov., paratype, slide no. YAH 13033; 22. L. pallidiptera sp. nov., paratype, slide no. YAH 13034; 23. L. taiwanensis sp. nov., paratype, slide no. YAH 13046; 24. L. rosataenia sp. nov., holotype, slide no. YAH 13042; 25. L. flavaterminata sp. nov., holotype, slide no. YAH 13039; 26. L. xanthacma (Meyrick, 1938), slide no. YAH 13051. (Scales = 0.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286111/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[465,497,548,572]" pageId="9" pageNumber="32" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Papillae anales setose, rounded posteriorly. Apophyses posteriores about twice length of apophyses anteriores. Eighth sternite with long setae on posterior margin, posterior half parallel laterally, anterior half gradually narrowed. Ostium bursae semicircular, open anteriorly, with a spine at each side curved inward. Antrum inverted trapezoidal. Ductus bursae granulous in inner wall, widened medially; ductus seminalis arising from between basal half of ductus bursae. Corpus bursae ovate; signum triangular, toothed, anterior margin concave inward and dentate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
